Package: plotPlotR
Type: Package
Title: Field experiment plot creation, segmentation and manipulation
Version: 0.1.05
Author: c(person("Aswin", "Singaram Natarajan", , "sin17m@csiro.au", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8981-6353")),
        person("Todd", "Collins", , "col469@csiro.au", role = c("ctb"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8981-6353")))
Maintainer: Aswin Singaram Natarajan <sin17m@csiro.au>
Description: Set of functions to easily create and manipulate field experiment 
    layout using "sf" and "dplyr" packages. Users can input sf objects or table 
    as data frame to generate plot boundaries from 4 corners or from center point 
    of plots etc. Users can move individual plots, rows or ranges. 
Imports:
    dplyr (>= 1.1.4),
    magrittr (>= 2.0.3),
    sf (>= 1.0-15)
Depends:
    R (>= 2.10)
License: AGPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.1
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/sin17m/plotplotr, https://sin17m.github.io/plotPlotR/
BugReports: https://github.com/sin17m/plotplotr/issues
